[edit]

All four of Connelly's brothers, Pat, Joe, Dan, and Kevin, work as scouts or managers in the NBA or college basketball. Pat was previously the assistant general manager of the Phoenix Suns, while Joe works for the Washington Wizards in player development, Dan is an advanced scout for the Utah Jazz, and Kevin runs a scouting service for high school players. Connelly is a fan of the Baltimore Ravens and Baltimore Orioles. Connelly is married to wife, Negah. They have two children.[14]

On June 17, 2013, Connelly was named as the executive vice president of basketball operations and general manager of the Denver Nuggets. In 2020, Connelly finished in ninth place for the Executive of the Year Award.[6]
